movieTitleCheck(String title)
Logic: Each word must start with an uppercase letter.

Test Cases:

movieTitleCheck("The Matrix") → true

movieTitleCheck("the Matrix") → false

movieTitleCheck("The matrix") → false

movieTitleCheck("TheMatrix") → true (1 word, starts with uppercase)

------------------------------------------------
movieIdLettersCheck(String[] line)
Logic: Movie ID prefix must match initials of title.

Test Cases:

movieIdLettersCheck(["The Matrix", "TM123"]) → true

movieIdLettersCheck(["The Matrix", "TX123"]) → false

movieIdLettersCheck(["Dark Knight", "DK123"]) → true

movieIdLettersCheck(["Dark Knight", "KD123"]) → false

------------------------------------------------
movieIdNumbersCheck(String id)
Logic:

Must be exactly 3 digits

Unique

Test Cases:

Input: "TM123" first time → true

Input: "TM123" second time → false (duplicate)

Input: "TM12" → false (only 2 digits)

Input: "TM1234" → false (too many digits)

------------------------------------------------
userNameCheck(String name)
Logic:

No leading spaces

Only alphabet and space allowed

Test Cases:

"Hassan Ali" → true

" Hassan Ali" → false (leading space)

"Hassan123" → false

"Hassan@Ali" → false

"Hassan" → true

--------------------------------------
userIdCheck(String id)
Logic:

Length = 9

First 8: digits

Last: alphanumeric

Unique

Test Cases:

"12345678X" → true

"12345678X" again → false (duplicate)

"1234567X" → false (only 8 chars)

"12345678@" → false (non-alphanumeric last char)

"ABCDEFGHX" → false (letters in first 8)

